---
const effectiveDate = "2025/09/04";
---

<main class="font-primary flex flex-col gap-9 py-20 px-10 md:px-30 lg:px-50">
  <div class="flex justify-center">
    <h1 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold mb-5 lg:mb-10">Privacy Policy</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="">
    <h2 class="font-bold text-2xl mb-2">Effective Date: {effectiveDate}</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      This Privacy Policy outlines how Open Labs Nepal collects, uses, and
      protects information related to your use of the platform.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="">
    <h2 class="font-bold text-2xl mb-2">1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      We do not collect personal data directly through this website. No sign-up
      or login is required to access lab work. When you contribute via GitHub,
      your GitHub username and any publicly associated metadata (e.g.,
      timestamps, repository activity) become part of the public contribution
      record.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="">
    <h2 class="font-bold text-2xl mb-2">2. Public Nature of Data</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      All uploaded content (lab work, code, documents) is publicly available via
      GitHub. Anyone can view, download, or reuse it, following the terms of the
      applicable open-source license.
    </p>
    <p class="font-bold text-xl">
      By submitting content, you acknowledge that:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc text-xl list-inside">
      <li>
        The data will be visible publicly and may be indexed by search engines.
      </li>
      <li>
        Deletion requests must be made via GitHub pull request or by contacting
        the repository maintainers.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="">
    <h2 class="font-bold text-2xl mb-2">3. Third-Party Links</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      Open Labs Nepal may contain links to third-party platforms such as GitHub.
      We are not responsible for their privacy practices. Please refer to their
      respective privacy policies.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="">
    <h2 class="font-bold text-2xl mb-2">4. Data Security</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      While we do not store user data directly, we follow best practices in
      securing our codebase and contribution pipelines to prevent unauthorized
      modifications.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="">
    <h2 class="font-bold text-2xl mb-2">5. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p class="text-xl">
      We may update these policies as the platform evolves. Continued use of the
      platform after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the new
      terms.
    </p>
  </div>
</main>